      <h2>How to Update Segment:</h2>
      <br>
      <h3 class="">Step One</h3>
      <p>
        Obtain token, corporate id, and api key, for more information,
        <a
          href="https://experienceleague.adobe.com/docs/analytics-learn/tutorials/apis/using-postman-to-make-adobe-analytics-2-0-api-requests.html?lang=en"
          >see the Adobe tutorial</a
        >
       
      </p>
      
      <h3 class="">Step Two</h3>
      <p>Once you have filled the above details. You can use one of three functions to update segments:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <b>Replace: </b> It replace the dimension definition. Example, if the
          Segment definition has a Page Name = "Home page" dimension, you can
          change it to Page Name = "Home"
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Regex:</b> You can use Regular Expression to replace dimension
          definition.
          <b>Use double escape <code>\\ </code>for any special character</b>.
          Example, <code>"\\|help\\|click\\|\\|\\|(.*)\\|</code>
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Add and Replace</b> It will place the replaced dimension definition beneath the old one. 
          It includes both the old and new dimension definitions.
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p>Input to fill further:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <b>Old:</b> Input old dimension definition that you want to change
        </li>
        <li><b>New:</b> Input new dimension definition</li>
        <li>
          <b>Dimension to update</b> Enter the name of the dimension you want to change. 
          Please, do not use prop or var. If prop15 = Page name, use Page name instead of prop15.
        </li>
      </ol>
